  "lines": [
    "[section:Verse 1]",
    "I [C]come from Alabama with my [G]banjo on my [C]knee",
    "I'm going to Louisiana, my [G7]true love for to [C]see",
    "It [C]rained all night the day I left, the [G]weather it was [C]dry",
    "The sun so hot I froze to death, [G7]Susanna don't you [C]cry",
    "",
    "[section:Chorus]",
    "[F]Oh Susanna, [C]oh don't you cry for [G]me",
    "I [C]come from Alabama with my [G7]banjo on my [C]knee",
    "",
    "[section:Verse 2]",
    "I [C]had a dream the other night when [G]everything was [C]still",
    "I thought I saw Susanna a-[G7]coming down the [C]hill",
    "A [C]buckwheat cake was in her mouth, a [G]tear was in her [C]eye",
    "Says I, I'm coming from the south, [G7]Susanna don't you [C]cry",
    "",
    "[section:Chorus]",
    "[F]Oh Susanna, [C]oh don't you cry for [G]me",
    "I [C]come from Alabama with my [G7]banjo on my [C]knee"
  ],
